width=30% | Image\n!width=45% | Status\n|-\n| [[House sparrow]]<br/>(''Passer domesticus'') ||<center>[[File:House sparrow (Passer domesticus).jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A resident breeding species \n|-\n| [[Spanish sparrow]]<br/>(''Passer hispaniolensis'') ||<center>[[File:Passer Hispaniolensis Male.JPG|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Eurasian tree sparrow]]<br/>(''Passer montanus'') ||<center>[[File:Tree Sparrow Japan Flip.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A resident breeding species \n|-\n| [[Rock sparrow]]<br/>(''Petronia petronia'') ||<center>[[File:Petronia petronia -Ariege, Midi-Pyrenee, France-8-4c.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|}\n\n==Wagtails and pipits==\n'''Order''': [[Passerine|Passeriformes]]{{nbsp|3}}'''Family''': [[Motacillidae]]\n\nMotacillidae is a family of small passerine birds with medium to long tails. They are slender, ground-feeding insectivores of open country. There are about 66 species worldwide, 15 in Britain.\n{| width=90% class=\"wikitable\"\n!width=25% | Common and binomial names\n!width=30% | Image\n!width=45% | Status\n|-\n| [[Western yellow wagtail]]<br/>(''Motacilla flava'') ||<center>[[File:Yellow Wagtail (5811285648).jpg|500x160px]]</center> || Seven races including:\n* Blue-headed wagtail ''M. f. flava'' (nominate subspecies occurring as a migrant)\n* Yellow wagtail ''M. f. flavissima'' (subspecies breeding in Britain)\n|-\n| [[Citrine wagtail]]<br/>(''Motacilla citreola'') ||<center>[[File:Citrine Wagtail (Motacilla citreola)- Breeding Male of calcarata race at Bharatpur I IMG 5752.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Grey wagtail]]<br/>(''Motacilla cinerea'') ||<center>[[File:Grey Wagtail.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A resident breeding species\n|-\n| [[White wagtail]]<br/>(''Motacilla alba'') ||<center>[[File:Pied Wagtail rear view 700.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A resident breeding species with two additional visiting races\n* ''M. a. alba'' (nominate subspecies occurring as a migrant)\