 bunting]]<br/>(''Emberiza fucata'') ||<center>[[File:Emberiza fucata.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Little bunting]]<br/>(''Emberiza pusilla'') ||<center>[[File:Little Bunting.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A scarce migrant\n|-\n| [[Yellow-breasted bunting]]<br/>(''Emberiza aureola'') ||<center>[[File:EmberizaAureolaF.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Chestnut bunting]]<br/>(''Emberiza rutila'') || || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Reed bunting]]<br/>(''Emberiza schoeniclus'') ||<center>[[File:Emberiza schoeniclus -England -male-8.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A resident breeding species \n|-\n| [[Pallas' reed bunting]]<br/>(''Emberiza pallasi'') ||<center>[[File:Emberiza pallasi (10).jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Black-headed bunting]]<br/>(''Emberiza melanocephala'') ||<center>[[File:28-090504-black-headed-bunting-at-first-layby.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Corn bunting]]<br/>(''Emberiza calandra'') ||<center>[[File:Emberiza calandra -Jardin des Plantes, Paris, France-8.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A resident breeding species \n|}\n\n==Icterids==\n'''Order''': [[Passerine|Passeriformes]]{{nbsp|3}}'''Family''': [[Icterid|Icteridae]]. \n\nThere are four rare vagrants in Britain.\n{| width=90% class=\"wikitable\"\n!width=25% | Common and binomial names\n!width=30% | Image\n!width=45% | Status\n|-\n| [[Bobolink]]<br/>(''Dolichonyx oryzivorus'') ||<center>[[File:Bobolink, Mer Bleue.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Brown-headed cowbird]]<br/>(''Molothrus ater'') ||<center>[[File:Molothrus ater 2.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Baltimore oriole]]<br/>(''Icterus galbula'') ||<center>[[File:Icterus-galbula-002.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Red-winged blackbird]]<br/>(''Agelaius phoeniceus'') ||<center>[[File:Agelaius phoeniceus2.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|}\n\n==New World warblers==\n'''Order''': [[Passerine|Passeriformes]]{{nbsp|3}}'''Family''': [[New_World_warbler|Parulidae]]\n\nA group of small, often colourful passerine birds restricted to the New World. Most are arboreal and insectivorous. There are about 118 species worldwide. Eighteen have occurred as vagrants in Britain.\n{| width=90% class=\"wikitable\"\n!width=25% | Common and binomial names\n!width=30% | Image\n!width=45% | Status\n|-\n| [[Ovenbird]]<br/>(''Seiurus aurocapilla'') ||<center>[[File:Ovenbird RWD2011b.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Northern waterthrush]]<br/>(''Parkesia noveboracensis'') ||<center>[[File:Seiurus noveboracensis MP1.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Golden-winged warbler]]<br/>(''Vermivora chrysoptera'') ||<center>[[File:Vermivora chrysoptera St Louis Missouri 1.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Black-and-white warbler]]<br/>(''Mniotilta varia'') ||<center>[[File:Black-and-white Warbler.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Tennessee warbler]]<br/>(''Oreothlypis peregrina'') ||<center>[[File:Tennessee Warbler 2.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Common yellowthroat]]<br/>(''Geothlypis trichas'') ||<center>[[File:Commonyellowthroat159.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Hooded warbler]]<br/>(''Setophaga citrina'') ||<center>[[File:Wilsonia citrina (Belize).jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[American redstart]]<br/>(''Setophaga ruticilla'') ||<center>[[File:Setophaga ruticilla -Chiquimula, Guatemala -male-8-4c.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Cape May warbler]]<br/>(''Setophaga tigrina'') ||<center>[[File:Dendroica tigrina FWS.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Northern parula]]<br/>(''Setophaga americana'') ||<center>[[File:Northern Parula in High Island by Dan Pancamo 1.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Magnolia warbler]]<br/>(''Setophaga magnolia'') ||<center>[[File:Dendroica magnolia MN.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Bay-breasted warbler]]<br/>(''Setophaga castanea'') ||<center>[[File:Dendroica-castanea-001.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Blackburnian warbler]]<br/>(''Setophaga fusca'') ||<center>[[File:Dendroica-fusca-001.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Yellow warbler]]<br/>(''Setophaga petechia'') ||<center>[[File:Dendroica-petechia-001.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Chestnut-sided warbler]]<br/>(''Setophaga pensylvanica'') ||<center>[[File:Dendroica-pensylvanica-003.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Blackpoll warbler]]<br/>(''Setophaga striata'') ||<center>[[File:BlackpollWarbler23.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Yellow-rumped warbler]]<br/>(''Setophaga coronata'') ||<center>[[File:Yellow-rump-capisic-spring-2012.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|-\n| [[Wilson's warbler]]<br/>(''Cardellina pusilla'') ||<center>[[File:Wilsonia pusilla.jpg|500x160px]]</center> || A rare vagrant\n|}\n\nThe links above lead to family accounts and individual species. [[Taxonomy (biology)|Taxonomy]] is very fluid in the age of [[DNA]] analysis, so other arrangements may be found, as in [[Sibley-Ahlquist taxonomy]].\n\n==Species awaiting acceptance==\nThe following species have been recorded recently and the British Ornithologists' Union Records Committee has not yet made a decision on whether to accept them onto the British List.<ref name=BOURC37>[https://archive.today/20121216133245/http://www3.interscience.wiley.com/cgi-bin/fulltext/121577421/HTMLSTART British Ornithologists' Union 37th report (October 2008)] ''Ibis'', 151 (1): 224-230.</ref>\n{| width=90% class=\"wikitable\"\n!width=25% | Common and binomial names\n!width=30% | Image\n!width=45% | Status\n|-\n| [[Brown booby]]<br/> (''Sula leucogaster'') || || A rare vagrant \n|-\n| [[Paddyfield pipit]]<br/> (''Anthus rufulus''){{Citation needed|date=December 2019}}|| || A rare vagrant \n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of non-native birds of Great Britain]]\n* [[List of birds of Leicestershire and Rutland]]\n* [[List of birds of Wales]]\n* [[List of birds of Ireland]]\n* [[British Birds Rarities Committee]]\n* ''[[British Birds (magazine)|British Birds]]'' (a long-established ornithology journal).\n* [[Birdwatching]]\n* [[European birds]]\n* [[Ornithology]]\n\n==Footnotes==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.bou.org.uk/british-list/ List of British birds published by The British Ornithologists' Union].\n*[https://www.doi.org/10.1046/j.0019-1019.2001.00026.x Taxonomic Recommendations for European Birds]\n*[https://www.doi.org/10.1046/j.1474-919x.2002.00110.x Taxonomic recommendations for British birds] (both in PDF format).\n*[http://www.rspb.org.uk The Royal Society for the Protection of Birds (RSPB)] and [http://www.rspb.org.uk/birds/guide RSPB A to Z of UK Birds]\n*''[http://www.britishbirds.co.uk/search?id=9283 Splitting headaches? Recent taxonomic changes affecting the British and Western Palaearctic lists]'' - Martin Collinson, ''[[British Birds (magazine)|British Birds]]'' vol 99 (June 2006), 306-323\n*[http://www.bto.org/volunteer-surveys/birdatlas/previous-atlases/previous-atlases British Trust for Ornithology surveys]\n\n{{Fauna of Great Britain}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of animals of the British Isles|Bird]]\n[[Category:Birds in the United Kingdom|'01]]\n[[Category:Lists of birds by location|Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Fauna of Great Britain|'birds]]\n[[Category:Lists of birds of Europe|Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Lists of biota of Great Britain|bird]]\n[[Category:Lists of birds by country|bird]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7f:ae21:6100:6538:47be:2647:dcf8", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Fixed typo)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_birds_of_Great_Britain"}
{"title_page": "Warren Cummings", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Warren Cummings\n| fullname    = Warren Thomas Cummings<ref>{{Hugman|4484|accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref>\n| height      = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1980|10|15|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Aberdeen]], Scotland\n| position    = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| years1      = 2000\u20132003 | clubs1  = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]                                    | caps1  = 0   | goals1  = 0\n| years2      = 2000\u20132001 | clubs2  = \u2192 [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] (loan)                 | caps2  = 10  | goals2  = 1\n| years3      = 2001      | clubs3  = \u2192 [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] (loan) | caps3  = 3   | goals3  = 0\n| years4      = 2001\u20132002 | clubs4  = \u2192 [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] (loan) | caps4  = 14  | goals4  = 0\n| years5      = 2002      | clubs5  = \u2192 [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] (loan)               | caps5  = 8   | goals5  = 0\n| years6      = 2002      | clubs6  = \u2192 [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] (loan)               | caps6  = 3   | goals6  = 0\n| years7      = 2003      | clubs7  = \u2192 [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] (loan)                 | caps7  = 16  | goals7  = 0\n| years8      = 2003\u20132012 | clubs8  = [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]]                          | caps8  = 234 | goals8  = 5\n| years9      = 2012      | clubs9  = \u2192 [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]] (loan)                 | caps9  = 9   | goals9  = 0\n| years10     = 2012\u20132013 | clubs10 = [[AFC Wimbledon]]                                           | caps10 = 9   | goals10 = 0\n| years11     = 2013      | clubs11 = [[Poole Town F.C.|Poole Town]]                              | caps11 = 6   | goals11 = 0\n| years12     = 2013\u20132016 | clubs12 = [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]]     | caps12 = 61  | goals12 = 1\n| totalcaps = 373 | totalgoals = 7\n| nationalyears1 = 2002   | nationalteam1 = [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]]| nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0   \n}}\n'''Warren Thomas Cummings''' (born 15 October 1980) is a Scottish former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]]. He played for [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]], [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]], [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]], [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]], [[AFC Wimbledon]], [[Poole Town F.C.|Poole Town]] and [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]]. Cummings also played once for the [[Scotland national football team]], in 2002.\n\n==Club career==\nCummings started his career at [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] but never made it into the first team, and instead was loaned out several times \u2013 [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] 2000\u201301,<ref>{{cite news|date=14 December 2000|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bournemouth/1070708.stm\n|title=Cummings extends Cherries loan spell|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] 2000\u201301 and 2001\u201302,<ref>{{cite news|date=26 July 2001|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/w/west_bromwich_albion/1458520.stm\n|title=West Brom secure Cummings loan|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> and [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] in 2002\u201303.<ref>{{cite news|date=23 August 2002|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/d/dundee_utd/2211876.stm|title=Cummings in Tayside move\n|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref>\n\nFollowing his return from the Dundee United loan spell, Cummings was again loaned to Bournemouth, for a three-month spell,<ref>{{cite news\n|date=11 February 2003|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bournemouth/2746801.stm|title=Cummings bids to lift Cherries\n|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> before signing a permanent deal with the club.<ref>{{cite news|date=16 April 2003\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bournemouth/2954349.stm|title=Cherries seal Cummings deal|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> He went on to make 23 appearances for \"The Cherries\" in that season, helping them win promotion via the playoffs. In the following season he established himself as a first team player, making 46 appearances in total and scoring 2 goals.\n\nThe 2004\u201305 season brought a playoff push for \"The Cherries\", with Cummings playing an important part and scoring 3 goals. However, during an away derby with [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]] in March 2005, he suffered a double broken leg in a crunch tackle by Swindon's [[Steve Jenkins]]. This was a major blow to both Cummings and Bournemouth, and was a major factor in them failing in their playoff bid. Nonetheless, Cummings signed a new deal with Bournemouth in the summer of 2006.<ref>{{cite news|date=13 June 2006\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bournemouth/5073214.stm|title=Cummings signs new Cherries deal|publisher=BBC Sport\n|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> He made his league return as a late substitute in the 3\u20130 defeat to [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]] at the start of the [[2006-07 in English football|2006\u201307]] campaign. In June 2007 Cummings signed a new two-year deal with Bournemouth.<ref>{{cite news\n|date=4 June 2007|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bournemouth/6721109.stm|title=Cummings signs new Cherries deal\n|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> He broke his arm in a 1\u20131 draw with [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] on 15 September 2007.<ref>{{cite news|date=15 September 2007|url=http://www.afcb.premiumtv.co.uk/page/InjuryLatest/0,,10324~1113255,00.html|title=Cummings Breaks Arm\n|publisher=A.F.C. Bournemouth|accessdate=17 September 2007}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 June 2012 it was announced that he has signed with [[Football League Two|League Two]] club [[AFC Wimbledon]].<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://www.afcwimbledon.co.uk/news.php?Psection_id=2&Psub_section_id=1&Open=7129#7129|title=New signing: Dons complete Warren Cummings deal\n|publisher=AFC Wimbledon|accessdate=29 June 2012}}</ref> He played a total of 9 league games for the \"Dons\" before being released from the club on 10 July 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=Warren leaves Wimbledon|url=http://www.afcwimbledon.co.uk/news/article/warren-departs-906768.aspx|publisher=AFC Wimbledon|accessdate=10 July 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 August 2013, Cummings joined [[Southern League Premier Division]] side [[Poole Town F.C.|Poole Town]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Poole Town sign Warren Cummings|url=http://www.pooletownfc.co.uk/poole-town-sign-warren-cummings/|publisher=Poole Town F.C.|accessdate=27 August 2013}}</ref>\n\nFor his services to AFC Bournemouth, Cummings received a testimonial match against [[AC Milan]] on 3 September 2016; the match marked the club debut for [[England national football team|England]] star [[Jack Wilshere]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/arsenals-jack-wilshere-made-bournemouth-8758304|publisher=Daily Mirror|date=3 September 2016|accessdate=3 September 2016|first=David|last=Cross|title=Arsenal's Jack Wilshere made Bournemouth transfer switch after advice from David Beckham}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nCummings won one [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] cap, when he played in a Far East tour game against the [[Hong Kong League XI]] in May 2002. Scotland won the Reunification Cup match 4\u20130.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/player_details.cfm?playerid=23178&CFID=996789&CFTOKEN=45205944\n|title=Player Details \u2013 Warren Cummings\n|publisher=[[Scottish Football Association]]\n|accessdate=7 August 2008}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*{{soccerway|warren-cummings/50347|name=Warren Cummings}}\n\n{{2004\u201305 Football League One Team of the Year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cummings, Warren}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Aberdeen]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Scottish footballers]]\n[[Category:Scotland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Chelsea F.C. players]]\n[[Category:A.F.C. Bournemouth players]]\n[[Category:West Bromwich Albion F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Dundee United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Crawley Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:AFC Wimbledon players]]\n[[Category:Poole Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Scotland under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Havant & Waterlooville F.C. players]]\n[[Category:People educated at Bridge of Don Academy]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Warren Cummings\n| fullname    = Warren Thomas Cummings<ref>{{Hugman|4484|accessdate=26 March 2017}}</ref>\n| height      = {{height|ft=5|in=9}}\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1980|10|15|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Aberdeen]], Scotland\n| currentclub =\n| clubnumber  = \n| position    = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| years1      = 2000\u20132003 | clubs1  = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]                                    | caps1  = 0   | goals1  = 0\n| years2      = 2000\u20132001 | clubs2  = \u2192 [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] (loan)                 | caps2  = 10  | goals2  = 1\n| years3      = 2001      | clubs3  = \u2192 [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] (loan) | caps3  = 3   | goals3  = 0\n| years4      = 2001\u20132002 | clubs4  = \u2192 [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] (loan) | caps4  = 14  | goals4  = 0\n| years5      = 2002      | clubs5  = \u2192 [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] (loan)               | caps5  = 8   | goals5  = 0\n| years6      = 2002      | clubs6  = \u2192 [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] (loan)               | caps6  = 3   | goals6  = 0\n| years7      = 2003      | clubs7  = \u2192 [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] (loan)                 | caps7  = 16  | goals7  = 0\n| years8      = 2003\u20132012 | clubs8  = [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]]                          | caps8  = 234 | goals8  = 5\n| years9      = 2012      | clubs9  = \u2192 [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]] (loan)                 | caps9  = 9   | goals9  = 0\n| years10     = 2012\u20132013 | clubs10 = [[AFC Wimbledon]]                                           | caps10 = 9   | goals10 = 0\n| years11     = 2013      | clubs11 = [[Poole Town F.C.|Poole Town]]                              | caps11 = 6   | goals11 = 0\n| years12     = 2013\u20132016 | clubs12 = [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.| Havant & Waterlooville]]     | caps12 = 61  | goals12 = 1\n| totalcaps = 373 | totalgoals = 7\n| nationalyears1 = 2002   | nationalteam1 = [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]]| nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0   \n}}\n'''Warren Thomas Cummings''' (born 15 October 1980) is a Scottish former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]]. He played for [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]], [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]], [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]], [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]], [[AFC Wimbledon]], [[Poole Town F.C.|Poole Town]] and [[Havant & Waterlooville F.C.|Havant & Waterlooville]].  Cummings also played once for the [[Scotland national football team]], in 2002.\n\n==Club career==\nCummings started his career at [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] but never made it into the first team, and instead was loaned out several times \u2013 [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]] 2000\u201301,<ref>{{cite news|date=14 December 2000|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bournemouth/1070708.stm\n|title=Cummings extends Cherries loan spell|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] 2000\u201301 and 2001\u201302,<ref>{{cite news|date=26 July 2001|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/w/west_bromwich_albion/1458520.stm\n|title=West Brom secure Cummings loan|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> and [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] in 2002\u201303.<ref>{{cite news|date=23 August 2002|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/d/dundee_utd/2211876.stm|title=Cummings in Tayside move\n|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref>\n\nFollowing his return from the Dundee United loan spell, Cummings was again loaned to Bournemouth, for a three-month spell,<ref>{{cite news\n|date=11 February 2003|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bournemouth/2746801.stm|title=Cummings bids to lift Cherries\n|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> before signing a permanent deal with the club.<ref>{{cite news|date=16 April 2003\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bournemouth/2954349.stm|title=Cherries seal Cummings deal|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> He went on to make 23 appearances for \"The Cherries\" in that season, helping them win promotion via the playoffs. In the following season he established himself as a first team player, making 46 appearances in total and scoring 2 goals.\n\nThe 2004\u201305 season brought a playoff push for \"The Cherries\", with Cummings playing an important part and scoring 3 goals. However, during an away derby with [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]] in March 2005, he suffered a double broken leg in a crunch tackle by Swindon's [[Steve Jenkins]]. This was a major blow to both Cummings and Bournemouth, and was a major factor in them failing in their playoff bid. Nonetheless, Cummings signed a new deal with Bournemouth in the summer of 2006.<ref>{{cite news|date=13 June 2006\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bournemouth/5073214.stm|title=Cummings signs new Cherries deal|publisher=BBC Sport\n|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> He made his league return as a late substitute in the 3\u20130 defeat to [[Chesterfield F.C.|Chesterfield]] at the start of the [[2006-07 in English football|2006\u201307]] campaign. In June 2007 Cummings signed a new two-year deal with Bournemouth.<ref>{{cite news\n|date=4 June 2007|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/bournemouth/6721109.stm|title=Cummings signs new Cherries deal\n|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=12 June 2007}}</ref> He broke his arm in a 1\u20131 draw with [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] on 15 September 2007.<ref>{{cite news|date=15 September 2007|url=http://www.afcb.premiumtv.co.uk/page/InjuryLatest/0,,10324~1113255,00.html|title=Cummings Breaks Arm\n|publisher=A.F.C. Bournemouth|accessdate=17 September 2007}}</ref> \n\nOn 29 June 2012 it was announced that he has signed with [[Football League Two|League Two]] club [[AFC Wimbledon]].<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://www.afcwimbledon.co.uk/news.php?Psection_id=2&Psub_section_id=1&Open=7129#7129|title=New signing: Dons complete Warren Cummings deal\n|publisher=AFC Wimbledon|accessdate=29 June 2012}}</ref> He played a total of 9 league games for the \"Dons\" before being released from the club on 10 July 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=Warren leaves Wimbledon|url=http://www.afcwimbledon.co.uk/news/article/warren-departs-906768.aspx|publisher=AFC Wimbledon|accessdate=10 July 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 August 2013, Cummings joined [[Southern League Premier Division]] side [[Poole Town F.C.|Poole Town]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Poole Town sign Warren Cummings|url=http://www.pooletownfc.co.uk/poole-town-sign-warren-cummings/|publisher=Poole Town F.C.|accessdate=27 August 2013}}</ref>\n\nFor his services to AFC Bournemouth, Cummings received a testimonial match against [[AC Milan]] on 3 September 2016; the match marked the club debut for [[England national football team|England]] star [[Jack Wilshere]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/arsenals-jack-wilshere-made-bournemouth-8758304|publisher=Daily Mirror|date=3 September 2016|accessdate=3 September 2016|first=David|last=Cross|title=Arsenal's Jack Wilshere made Bournemouth transfer switch after advice from David Beckham}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nCummings won one [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] cap, when he played in a Far East tour game against the [[Hong Kong League XI]] in May 2002. Scotland won the Reunification Cup match 4\u20130.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://www.scottishfa.co.uk/player_details.cfm?playerid=23178&CFID=996789&CFTOKEN=45205944\n|title=Player Details \u2013 Warren Cummings\n|publisher=[[Scottish Football Association]]\n|accessdate=7 August 2008}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*{{soccerway|warren-cummings/50347|name=Warren Cummings}}\n\n{{2004\u201305 Football League One Team of the Year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cummings, Warren}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Aberdeen]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Scottish footballers]]\n[[Category:Scotland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Chelsea F.C. players]]\n[[Category:A.F.C. Bournemouth players]]\n[[Category:West Bromwich Albion F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Dundee United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Crawley Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:AFC Wimbledon players]]\n[[Category:Poole Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Scotland under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Havant & Waterlooville F.C. 